                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">ʿAbdā Alaha, priest,
                        was tortured with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1100">ʿAbdishōʿ</persName> by Ardashir, brother of Sapor; ʿAbdā was arrested
                        with seven friends and seven virgins. Barḥaḏbshabā and Samuel also were
                        executed. Then ʿAbdishōʿ and ʿAbdā Alaha were executed. They were buried by
                        Byzantine slaves in a neighboring village. He was martyred with 38
                        companions.</note>
